<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="propose-v">propose <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /prə'pəʊz/    美 /prə'poʊz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[正式用语] 提出；提议；建议</strong></h4>
<p>to formally suggest sth as a possible plan or action：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>propose a better solution
提出更好的解决方案</p></div>

<ul>
<li>propose doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The report proposes extending motorways.
该报告建议拓宽机动车道。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>propose + that … (should) do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A professor at the Academy has proposed that a fund (should) be established to raise money.
学院的一位教授提议设立基金会来募集资金。</p><footer>外研⑦ – 6</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[正式用语] 打算；计划</strong></h4>
<p>to intend to do sth：</p>
<ul>
<li>propose doing / to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He proposed buying / to buy a new car.
他打算买一辆新车。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>求婚：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve <strong>proposed marriage</strong> to her.
我已经向她求婚了。</p></div></div>